sources.title: King of the Zombies 1941 (Horror, Comedy) Human sacrifices! Savage torture! Voodoo rites!
sources.description:
On a haunted island where the living dread the dead!
When a group of travelers becomes stranded on a mysterious island, they must confront a mad scientist who uses voodoo to resurrect the dead and create an army of zombies.

Original title: King of the Zombies (1941)

Black & White version: https://youtu.be/Z2Royl-3MjE

Director: Jean Yarbrough
Writer: Edmond Kelso
Genres: Colorized, Adventure, Comedy, Horror, 

Main Cast: 
Dick Purcell as James McCarthy
Joan Woodbury as Barbara Winslow
Mantan Moreland as Jefferson 'Jeff' Jackson
Henry Victor as Dr. Miklos Sangre
John Archer as  Bill Summes


00:00 Full Movie (with subtitles)
1:00 A strange encounter at a remote island mansion unveils dark secrets and supernatural forces.
9:37 Unexpected visitors meet a mysterious island doctor and uncover the chilling truth about zombies and magic potions.
16:09 Unsettling rituals and forbidden knowledge surface as the guests delve deeper into the island's mysteries.
22:18 Voodoo rites, zombies, and hidden motives entangle the group in a dangerous island conspiracy.
29:29 Ghosts, zombies, and a secret radio transmitter add to the mounting terror on the island.
36:23 Suspicion and hidden secrets collide, as eerie events unravel on this isolated island.
42:14 Hypnosis, zombies, and a missing person deepen the mystery as the group searches for answers.
51:00 A man falls ill with a deadly fever, sparking a series of eerie occurrences tied to voodoo and zombies.
58:50 The group faces a deadly mix of voodoo rituals and zombie threats as danger tightens its grip on the island.
